Task no.01
----------
1) 1) //float r=2.5f % 2; //0.5 --commented ----> how is this 0.5 comes as result?

        float r = 2.5f / 2; //1.25
        System.out.println(r);
    
    ------>  output =1.25

  EXPLATION
-------------

 *  2.5f is a floating-point literal representing the number  2.5.
 *  is the modulus operator, which calculates the remainder when the left operand (2.5f) is divided by the right operand ('2').
 *  2 is an integer literal.
 * The result of the modulus operation (2.5f % 2) is assigned to the variable r, which is declared as a float.
 * Finally, the value of r (which is 0.5) is printed to the console.


