Task no.02
-----------
2) Write a program for the below mentioned scenario?

23 ==> 2+3=5
54 ==> 5+4=9
33 ==> 3+3=9
19 ==> 1+9=10=1+0 // no need for this
//55,65 - no need

int r=14; //use only literals  (hardcoded values)


public class SumOfDigits {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] numbers = {23, 54, 33, 43, 31};
        for (int number;)

            int tens = number / 10;
            int ones = number % 10;
            int sum = tens + ones;
            System.out.println("Sum of the digits " + number + " ==> " + tens + "+" + ones + " ==> " + sum)
} 


OUTPUT=
--------
23 ==> 2+3 ==> 5
54 ==> 5+4 ==> 9
33 ==> 3+3 ==> 6
43 ==> 4+3 ==> 7
31 ==> 3+1 ==> 4

